Deprecated Interfaces
sailpoint.object.IntegrationExecutor
          

The interface of a class that must be registered with an IntegrationConfig to process requests to an IDM system.

You should no longer use this interface. Use sailpoint.integration.AbstractIntegrationExecutor instead.

sailpoint.workflow.IdentityLibrary.getTestIdentity(WorkflowContext, String)
          

Build a detached copy of an Identity that we can use for policy checking and other questionable medical experiments.

If we find an existing Identity with the given name we clone it to make sure that changes don't get persisted. If there is no existing identity, this is assumed to be a new identity being created in LCM and we just make a stub.

sailpoint.object.Application.Feature.NO_DIRECT_PERMISSIONS_PROVISIONING
          Application.Feature.NO_GROUP_PERMISSIONS_PROVISIONING 
sailpoint.object.Application.Feature.NO_GROUP_PERMISSIONS_PROVISIONING
          Application.Feature.NO_PERMISSIONS_PROVISIONING Deprecated as of 6.4 in favor of NO_PERMISSIONS_PROVISIONING. This now lives on the Schema Feature Strings

Indicates that the connector cannot provision direct or target permissions for groups. When DIRECT_PERMISSIONS and PROVISIONING features are present, it is assumed that the connector can also provision direct permissions. This feature disables that assumption and causes permission request to be converted to work items for groups.
